OL,3,CLiberal Democrats celebrate after
OL,4,Ctaking top target Stockport Council
OL,6,FStockport Council will be led by a
OL,7,Fmajority party for the first time in
OL,8,F15 years, after the Liberal Democrats
OL,9,Fachieved one of their top targets.
OL,11,FSir Ed Davey's party had campaigned
OL,12,Fhard in the borough, having come close
OL,13,Fto taking overall control before.
OL,15,FMeanwhile Labour have seen huge losses
OL,16,Facross the board, while Reform UK made
OL,17,Fgains in most areas.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/9
